ce:section.ce:para:
The analysis of Ruggeri et al. [9] and the studies of other research groups [5,6] have shown that a few elements can be used as candidates for partial substitution of Mg and Ni, and the elements should have properties such as:

(i)

a higher vacancy formation energy than Mg [10];


(ii)

they can form a passive film or oxide layer on the Mg-based alloy;


(iii)

the passive film is compact;


(iv)

the passive film is resistant to the penetration of KOH solution;


(v)

the passive film has some ability of hydrogen diffusion;


(vi)

improved ability to avoid cracking on cycling.
